  "original_title": "\u201cMaybe this is life\u201d : Chinese Ambassadors response to delayed arrival of Yuan Wang 5",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\u201cMaybe this is life\u201d : Chinese Ambassadors response to delayed arrival of Yuan Wang 5",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Qi Zhenhong, the Chinese Ambassador to Sri Lanka said that the Hambantota Port was not only a major Belt and Road cooperation project, but is also a symbol of China \u2013 Sri Lanka friendship.",
        "The Chinese Ambassador to Sri Lanka speaking to reporters in Hambantota following the arrival of the Yuan Wang 5 Chinese Research / Survey vessel said that is a normal visit, and it nothing special.",
        "In response to a question posed on concerns raised by India over the arrival of the vessel, he said \"I think you can ask those questions from the Indian friends.\"",
        "His reponse to a question on the diplimatic tussle over the past few days over the vessel was \"I don't know. Maybe this is life. This is nature.\"",
        "\u201cMaybe this is life\u201d : Chinese Ambassadors response to delayed arrival of Yuan Wang 5"
      ],
